    "body": "Update: as per @zelig's suggestion I tried using web3.toWei, which works for small amounts (I tested `web3.toWei(0.00001, \"ether\")`, which worked fine).  However, when I attempt to send a larger amount (100 ether), I get the same issue:\n\n``` javascript\n> eth.sendTransaction({\n..    from: \"0x63524e3fe4791aefce1e932bbfb3fdf375bfad89\",\n..    to: \"0x1c11aa45c792e202e9ffdc2f12f99d0d209bef70\",\n..    value: web3.toWei(100, \"ether\")\n..  });\n'0xf067aa5af29c3a1e4fdd5cc7213d800079a67cd06b515ad5639f7b3e0742192e'\n\n> eth.getTransaction(\"0xf067aa5af29c3a1e4fdd5cc7213d800079a67cd06b515ad5639f7b3e0742192e\")\n{\n  value: '7766279631452241920',\n  gas: 90000,\n  gasPrice: '10000000000000',\n  input: '0x',\n  nonce: '0x15',\n  blockNumber: 137601,\n  from: '0x63524e3fe4791aefce1e932bbfb3fdf375bfad89',\n  to: '0x1c11aa45c792e202e9ffdc2f12f99d0d209bef70',\n  hash: '0xf067aa5af29c3a1e4fdd5cc7213d800079a67cd06b515ad5639f7b3e0742192e',\n  blockHash: '0xa168c3e6cbf2bf0ca9dc4806063279f79e7d593037b063b3c3d26561f919c1e0',\n  transactionIndex: 0\n}\n```\n\n7.76 ether again.  Maybe this is a BigNumber issue?\n",
